org.javafp.parsecj

Class Combinators

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.javafp.parsecj.Combinators

  • public abstract class Combinators
extends Object
    A collection of parser combinator functions. The Parser type along with retn & bind constitute a monad.

        public static <S,A,B> Parser<S,B> bind(Parser<S,? extends A> p,
                                       Function<A,Parser<S,B>> f)
        Monadic bind function. Bind chains two parsers by creating a parser which calls the first, and if that parser succeeds the resultant value is passed to the function argument to obtain a second parser, which is then invoked.
        Type Parameters:
        S - the input symbol type
        A - the first parser value type
        B - the second parser value type
        Parameters:
        p - a parser which is called first
        f - a function which is passed the result of the first parser if successful, and which returns a second parser
        Returns:
        the parser
